results.raw: Man Fatally Shot in Frogtown at 600 Blair Ave, Saint Paul, Minnesota, 55103
results.title: Man Fatally Shot in Frogtown

-MxMQHRJvLveS8jGO_Xx.text: Police have a crime scene established where the man was found deceased following a shooting.

-MxMR5Fts0uron0t9Wyv.text: A tweet from the SPD stated there is an active investigation ongoing where the victim was found.

-MxMYdnuwCzr80-cvyAN.text: According to a press release from Saint Paul police, the man was pronounced dead upon EMS arrival to the scene at around 11:30 a.m. Homicide investigators and the Forensics Services Unit (FSU) continue to process the crime scene. No arrests have been made.

nib.text:
A man was fatally shot in Frogtown Friday afternoon, officials said. 

At around 11:30 a.m. police responded to a report of an unconscious man lying in a backyard of a home in the 600 block of Blair Avenue.

Upon arrival, officers discovered the man who had been shot.   Medics arrived and pronounced the victim deceased. 

According to a report from the SPPD, homicide detectives assumed control of the investigation. 

No arrests were reported. 

The Ramsey County medical examiner will identify the victim and determine the cause of death.
